			<div id="rightCol">
		
				<h2 class="headline">Memorium</h2>
				<h2>Lisa Lewis</h2>

				<p>
		<img src="images/photos/memoriumPics/lisa-lewis.jpg" class="rightPic" width="300" />		
	
		<p>Lisa Ann Lewis, 47, of North Fort Myers passed away on July 14, 2013. She was born on September 23, 1965 in Detroit, Michigan. She has worked for Fort Myers Police Department as a Dispatch 911 Operator for over 26 years.</p>
		<p>Lisa has a Bachelors Degree in Criminal Justice from Mount St. Mary's University in Emmitsburg, MD. She was very active with the Fort Myers Police Department, Respect for Law Camp, and Relay For Life.</p>
		<p>Lisa is survived by her loving family including her father, Donald Lewis of North Fort Myers; maternal aunts, Patricia (Jerry) Kehoe of Fort Myers and Peggy Kelly of Plantation, FL; uncle, James Sweeney of Avon, New Jersey; aunt, Mary Sweeny of Red Bank, New Jersey; many cousins; and her extended Fort Myers Police Department and Public Safety Professional family. She is preceded in death by her mother, Barbara Lewis and sister, Margaret. </p>
		<p>Lisa was an Angel on Earth, and lived life to the fullest every single day, despite battling a life long illness.</p>
	</p>
				
				<br/>
				
